Project Flow diagram:

Users
  |
  v
Route 53 (DNS)
  |
  v
Application Load Balancer (ALB)
  |
  v
Kubernetes Ingress / API Gateway
  |
  v
------------------------------------------------
|            Amazon EKS Cluster                |
|                                              |
|  Order Service        Billing Service        |
|  Payment Service      Catalog Service        |
|  User Service         ... (55+ services)     |
|                                              |
|  (Docker Containers running as Pods)         |
------------------------------------------------
  |
  v
Databases (RDS / DynamoDB – per service)
_____________________________________________________
CI/CD Flow (Jenkins)

Developer
   |
   v
Git Repository
   |
   v
Jenkins Pipeline
   |
   |-- Build & Test
   |-- Docker Image Build
   |-- Push to Amazon ECR
   |
   v
Deploy to EKS (Helm / kubectl)

________________________________________
Async Communication Flow (Order → Billing)
Order Service
      |
      v
AWS SQS / SNS
      |
      v
Billing Service

_____________________________________________________
Monitoring & Logging Flow
EKS Cluster
     |
     v
CloudWatch Logs & Metrics
     |
     v
Prometheus  →  Grafana
__________________________________
“Traffic flows from users through Route 53 and ALB to EKS, where microservices run as containers. Jenkins handles CI/CD, images are stored in ECR, services communicate via SQS, 
and monitoring is done using CloudWatch and Grafana.”
